<TITLE> Northern trains halted after goods train derails at Gazipur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)Fourteen bogeys of a goods train bound for Mymensingh from Dhaka derailed at the outer signal of Joydevpur railway junction in Gazipur on Saturday. As a result, train services from Dhaka to north Bengal remained suspended. Joydevpur railway junction official, Gazi Ashraful Alam, told bdnews24.com the train derailed at around 2.30 pm. "A rescue train arrived from Dhaka at 6pm and rescue work is on," he said at around 8pm. Alam said it could take up to four more hours to clear the track. bdnews
